,Not Recommended,461560,29817505,Posted: 9 February,all,Helen Keller,"It's chill and Zen and whatnot, but... it reminds me too much of those side-scrollers on the Nintendo growing up. The ones I could never beat because I didn't have good enough hand-eye coordination.I want to like it. I don't care for the music, but it seems like a game where you just kinda figure stuff out as you go along. And apparently the game is beatable in ~30 minutes. As I have put over an hour into this, I seem to be one of those folks who can't figure out ""obvious"" methods (probably by using Youtube or whatnot). But it also frustrates me. You can access the map at specific points, but after my last fall from a really high-up point where I missed one stupid jump onto a thin podium out of about 57, and then thought I could land on something but then saw I couldn't and tried to land on something else... and I basically fell from the top left of the map to the complete bottom. Into water. And I really had no idea how to find another map area, or get back to where I was.Pros: Cool theme, chill ideas, I'd probably put more if I owned a Nintendo growing up and didn't rely on my 3 minutes of fail before I died and handed the controller to my friend who owned it til (s)he died... which was like 30+ minutes later.Cons: The music clangs, and I really don't care enough to bother to understand what's going on here. I've found the game too frustrating with the lack of anything specified (I mean ffs, I'm a block of stone, why not just sit there?). Weird (and possibly disturbing) pictures of lungs. Cryptic messages that go over my head. And I'm not even blonde -- though I suspect that I just can't get into the game to care enough. Maybe it's because I don't do mind-altering/recreational/illegal substances?Overall, hey it's free, the graphics are kinda cool (as is the map), the idea isn't half bad, and for a game beatable in under 30 minutes, it's already taken over an hour of my life. So I guess it's okay... but honestly, I wouldn't recommend it without a huge disclaimer: if you want to figure out a game that's chill with no real purpose aside from traipsing around Tibet with monks giving you cryptic rhymes... then do it!That, and my recommendation would be based on the person I am talking to.3/10"
