,Recommended,461560,29600586,Posted: 31 January,all,ArtisticFace,"I really liked this game and I thought it looked like a lot of time and love went into it from the developers. A quick and peaceful game that isn't hard and isn't easy, it gives you your own reign over the area to do whatever fits your fancy. You can achievment hunt, look for lore, or go for completeing it. My favorite parts were that it was a nice bite size game and I really dig the aesthetic of the game as a whole. I want to learn more about the small world they built!I would absolutely recommend this game, it's free and really nice if you have a couple ten minutes to spare on something unique. Personally, I wouldn't mind paying a dollar or two even though its short, its a neat game."
