76561198124553963,Recommended,461560,29508265,Posted: 26 January,all,Mr.Peabody,"Mandagon is a perfect example of how heart and story can carry a game. Games aren't great because of their graphics, gore, fantasy, etc... but because of the story they tell. This game tells a very complex story simply and lets the player discover what is going piece by piece causing them to want to continue playing to learn about the character. This heart and storytelling is an aspect of gaming that I would like to see more of. With advances in technology many developers have relied on graphical content to carry their games, but completely forgot about the reason why we should play their game. Games have evolved into a medium for storytelling and this game proves that you can successfully get a message across without fancy asthetics and long drawn out quick time events. It also shows (by the already overwhelmingly positive reviews) that gamers want to care about their characters and the story they tell. I hope to see more games like this in the future and would love to see this developer's future projects."
